  "text": "The Django admin filter rendering pipeline constructs empty related-field filters through a multi-stage process:\n\n1. **Filter Class Definition** (`django/contrib/admin/filters.py`):\n   - The base `ListFilter` class (line 26) defines the abstract `has_output()` method (lines 41-47) that determines whether a filter should be displayed.\n   - The `RelatedFieldListFilter` class (line 222) is responsible for rendering ForeignKey filter dropdowns. It inherits from `FieldListFilter` and overrides `has_output()` (lines 248-253) to check: `len(self.lookup_choices) + extra > 1`, where `extra` is 1 if `include_empty_choice` is True (accounting for the \"(None)\" choice for nullable fields).\n\n2. **Filter Collection and Filtering** (`django/contrib/admin/views/main.py`):\n   - The `ChangeList` class (line 67) collects and filters specifications in its `get_filters()` method (line 175).\n   - At line 221, each filter spec's `has_output()` method is called: `if spec and spec.has_output():`\n   - Only filters returning True are appended to `filter_specs` (line 222), which becomes `self.filter_specs`.\n\n3. **Template Rendering** (`django/contrib/admin/templates/admin/change_list.html` and `django/contrib/admin/templatetags/admin_list.py`):\n   - The `change_list.html` template (line 72) iterates over `cl.filter_specs`: `{% for spec in cl.filter_specs %}{% admin_list_filter cl spec %}{% endfor %}`\n   - Since only filters with `has_output() == True` are in `filter_specs`, filters are automatically hidden if they have insufficient choices.\n   - The `admin_list_filter` template tag (line 521 in `admin_list.py`) renders each filter spec using its template (spec.template), typically `admin/filter.html`.\n\nEmpty related-field filters are constructed in `RelatedFieldListFilter.__init__()` (lines 223-238 of filters.py), where `self.lookup_choices` is populated via `self.field_choices()`. These filters remain in the filter pipeline but are excluded from the sidebar display by the `has_output()` visibility control in `ChangeList.get_filters()` at line 221."
}

